>
  <main id="main">
<header class="page-hero"><div class="container"><div class="breadcrumbs"><a href="index.html">Home</a> / Missions</div><span class="kicker">Work of public consequence</span><h1>Humanity-scale missions demand disciplined service</h1><p>US Fellows organizes its work around enduring challenges where exceptional people can advance humanity, civil society, science, and the nation.</p></div></header>
<nav class="anchor-nav" aria-label="On this page"><div class="container"><a href="#humanity">Humanity</a><a href="#science">Science</a><a href="#earth">Earth</a><a href="#education">Education</a><a href="#civic">Civic Life</a><a href="#technology">Technology</a><a href="#capacity">National Capacity</a></div></nav>
<section class="section"><div class="container"><div class="section-intro section-intro--center"><span class="eyebrow">Mission Framework</span><h2>Not campaigns. Enduring areas of service.</h2><div class="rule"></div><p>Each mission provides a public-purpose context for fellowship appointments, host partnerships, research affiliations, convenings, and Society thought leadership.</p></div><div class="grid grid--2">
<article class="card" id="humanity"><div class="card__icon"><LegacyIcon name="heartbeat" /></div><h3>Humanity & Human Dignity</h3><p>Humanitarian service, immigrant communities, poverty, public health, access, civil society, and human flourishing.</p></article><article class="card" id="science"><div class="card__icon"><LegacyIcon name="flask" /></div><h3>Science & Discovery</h3><p>Scientific inquiry, frontier research, evidence, science communication, and discovery in service to public understanding.</p></article><article class="card" id="earth"><div class="card__icon"><LegacyIcon name="leaf" /></div><h3>Climate & Planetary Stewardship</h3><p>Climate resilience, conservation, biodiversity, environmental justice, sustainability, and stewardship of the living world.</p></article><article class="card" id="education"><div class="card__icon"><LegacyIcon name="book" /></div><h3>Education & Human Potential</h3><p>Learning, schools, youth opportunity, mentorship, workforce dignity, and the systems that help people flourish.</p></article><article class="card"><div class="card__icon"><LegacyIcon name="handshake-o" /></div><h3>Immigration & Opportunity</h3><p>Belonging, institutional access, civic participation, human mobility, and pathways to shared prosperity.</p></article><article class="card" id="civic"><div class="card__icon"><LegacyIcon name="institution" /></div><h3>Civic Life & Public Trust</h3><p>Public institutions, legal access, civic innovation, democratic culture, administration, and community resilience.</p></article><article class="card" id="technology"><div class="card__icon"><LegacyIcon name="code" /></div><h3>Technology for Public Good</h3><p>Responsible systems, public-interest technology, digital access, civic tools, and innovation directed toward human needs.</p></article><article class="card"><div class="card__icon"><LegacyIcon name="medkit" /></div><h3>Public Health & Human Security</h3><p>Health systems, preparedness, prevention, community wellbeing, safety, and the foundations of human security.</p></article><article class="card" id="capacity"><div class="card__icon"><LegacyIcon name="shield" /></div><h3>National Capacity & Resilience</h3><p>Infrastructure, cybersecurity, emergency preparedness, scientific capacity, public systems, and institutional strength.</p></article><article class="card"><div class="card__icon"><LegacyIcon name="hourglass-half" /></div><h3>Future Generations</h3><p>Long-term thinking, intergenerational responsibility, emerging risks, and institutions built to endure.</p></article>
  </div></div></section>
<section class="section section--navy"><div class="container"><div class="grid grid--2"><div><span class="eyebrow">From Mission to Appointment</span><h2>A framework for action</h2><div class="rule"></div><p>A mission becomes tangible through a qualified host, a defined project, a capable Fellow, and an accountable contribution.</p></div><div><ul class="check-list"><li>Identify an institutional need of public consequence</li><li>Define the intended public benefit</li><li>Match the contribution to a Fellow’s field and capacity</li><li>Establish supervision, scope, and responsible practice</li><li>Document lessons and strengthen future work</li></ul></div></div></div></section>
<section class="section"><div class="container"><div class="cta"><div><h2>Bring a mission into the Society.</h2><p>Institutions may propose a project, research affiliation, civic initiative, or service opportunity for consideration.</p></div><div class="actions"><a class="button button--gold" href="submit-opportunity.html">Submit an Opportunity</a><a class="button button--outline" href="become-a-host.html">Host a Fellow</a></div></div></div></section>
<section class="section section--mist"><div class="container"><div class="section-intro"><span class="eyebrow">How missions are chosen</span><h2>Enduring need, credible leverage, public value</h2><div class="rule"></div><p>A Society mission is broad enough to matter across years and institutions, but it must also reveal practical places where individual expertise can make a responsible contribution.</p></div><div class="grid grid--3"><article class="card"><h3>Enduring consequence</h3><p>The issue affects human dignity, shared knowledge, civic capacity, living systems, or the institutions on which communities depend.</p></article><article class="card"><h3>Room for contribution</h3><p>There are bounded questions, projects, research needs, operating challenges, or partnerships where a Fellow’s capabilities can be useful.</p></article><article class="card"><h3>Potential to strengthen capacity</h3><p>The work can leave behind knowledge, tools, relationships, methods, or institutional ability that extends beyond one intervention.</p></article></div></div></section>
<section class="section"><div class="container"><div class="grid grid--2"><div><span class="eyebrow">Working across missions</span><h2>Complex needs rarely stay in one category</h2><div class="rule"></div><p>Public health may depend on civic trust. Climate resilience may depend on infrastructure, education, and public-interest technology. Scientific capacity may require policy, communication, and workforce development.</p></div><div><p>Mission categories provide orientation, not silos. An appointment may draw from several fields while remaining accountable to a primary purpose, a defined host, and a scope that can be managed responsibly.</p><p>This cross-mission view helps the Society assemble the right perspectives without losing clarity about who is responsible for what.</p></div></div></div></section>
</main>

</BaseLayout>
